## ============================================================
## 7. KEY LEARNINGS & GOTCHAS
## ============================================================

1. ECV endpoint naming is NOT intuitive:
   - The working endpoint is just "enhanced-match", not any variation of
     "register-enhanced-match-mobile-otp" or "register-enhanced-matchmobile-otp"

2. ECV response field names have TRAILING UNDERSCORES:
   - stageOneId_ (not stgOneHitId or stageOneId)
   - stageTwoId_ (not stgTwoHitId or stageTwoId)

3. Content-Type matters:
   - ECV: application/x-www-form-urlencoded (body is URLSearchParams)
   - BRE: application/json (body is JSON)
   - Token: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

4. The working ECV curl has a trailing --data-urlencode '=' parameter

5. PAN value in test data is SCXPF1234J (J at end), not SCXPF1234I (I at end)

6. Port mapping: local 3001 -> external 3000 (backend), local 5000 -> external 80 (main app)

7. Token expiry is 1800s (30 min), we cache for 1680s (28 min) to refresh early

8. Experian UAT can be flaky - 500 errors may be temporary server issues on their side

9. Cookie headers appeared in working curl (Incapsula WAF) but are NOT needed
   when calling from server-side - those are browser-specific WAF cookies
